1
00:00:48,740 --> 00:00:51,710
(Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism
and the Korea Creative Content Agency)

2
00:00:52,610 --> 00:00:56,820
Recent disappearances have been reported
in and around Guam City.

3
00:00:57,250 --> 00:01:00,320
It's been reported that over ten people
have been confirmed missing.

4
00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:02,960
- How am I supposed to pay you back...
- Police suspect violent crime,

5
00:01:02,960 --> 00:01:04,860
- if I don't make any money?
- not just disappearances...

6
00:01:05,290 --> 00:01:08,560
Hey, you think this is all on me?
That's on you for lending it to me.

7
00:01:08,930 --> 00:01:12,130
Whatever. Sue me!
Goodness, you just can't stop talking.

8
00:01:12,670 --> 00:01:14,230
Gosh, just hang up!

9
00:01:20,010 --> 00:01:21,140
Darn, it's all soaked.

10
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:34,550
Aren't you Hong Jae Gwang?

11
00:01:38,790 --> 00:01:39,830
Who on earth are you?

12
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:42,630
I said, "Who are you?"

13
00:01:48,170 --> 00:01:49,170
My gosh.

14
00:01:55,810 --> 00:01:57,080
What's going on?

15
00:03:36,310 --> 00:03:38,040
(Police SWAT team)

16
00:03:38,110 --> 00:03:41,080
We'll search for the missing victims
as soon as the suspect is in custody.

17
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:43,580
Turning left, entering the approach route.

18
00:03:48,990 --> 00:03:50,420
All agents, move out!

19
00:03:54,030 --> 00:03:55,030
Begin the operation.

20
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:04,470
(Yeonpung Inn)

21
00:04:26,730 --> 00:04:29,200
Hey, Prosecutor Cha.
Why did you come all the way in here?

22
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:33,070
You promised you'd just watch.
It's dangerous. All right?

23
00:04:33,870 --> 00:04:36,100
Don't be difficult.
Please go back outside.

24
00:04:36,670 --> 00:04:38,440
This isn't even your case, Prosecutor Cha.

25
00:04:39,370 --> 00:04:40,410
Goodness.

26
00:04:51,050 --> 00:04:53,120
- Police! Don't move!
- Don't move!

27
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:04,430
Are you Lee Woo Gyeom?

28
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:25,150
A pleasure.

29
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:27,350
Prosecutor Cha Yi Yeon.

30
00:05:31,590 --> 00:05:32,990
But we have a problem.

31
00:05:34,030 --> 00:05:35,660
You're here much earlier than I expected.

32
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:37,900
Could you give me five more minutes?

33
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,030
I'm still treating a patient.

34
00:05:42,540 --> 00:05:43,570
Would you like to see?

35
00:05:43,870 --> 00:05:45,970
- What are you doing? Don't move.
- No, I'll be done in a second.

36
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,410
I said, "Don't move!"

37
00:05:48,870 --> 00:05:51,340
All right. I'll stay perfectly still.

38
00:05:53,110 --> 00:05:55,110
Drop what's in your hand
and cooperate with us.

39
00:05:59,820 --> 00:06:00,820
Arrest him.

40
00:06:05,020 --> 00:06:08,430
You have the right to remain silent
and to an attorney,

41
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:11,400
anything you say from this point on
will be used as evidence.

42
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:14,500
Get the forensics team in here
and tend to the victim.

43
00:06:15,030 --> 00:06:17,900
- Check for any other victims.
- Yes, sir.

44
00:06:25,140 --> 00:06:26,150
Prosecutor Cha.

45
00:06:27,650 --> 00:06:29,320
Don't let anyone else
operate on the patient.

46
00:06:31,220 --> 00:06:32,220
What was that?

47
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:34,790
If my surgical methods get mixed up
with another's,

48
00:06:35,690 --> 00:06:37,260
they'll never recover.

49
00:06:38,290 --> 00:06:39,630
What are you talking about?

50
00:06:40,630 --> 00:06:43,460
You wouldn't understand
even if I explained it now.

51
00:06:45,430 --> 00:06:46,930
I'm telling you, don't let them get
any other treatment.

52
00:06:48,630 --> 00:06:49,840
You went to great lengths to find him.

53
00:06:50,540 --> 00:06:51,640
You can't have him dying on us.

54
00:07:30,380 --> 00:07:32,810
(Yeonpung Inn)

55
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:35,380
Multiple bodies found scattered.

56
00:07:35,950 --> 00:07:38,180
One surviving victim, condition unknown.

57
00:07:38,780 --> 00:07:40,850
- Requesting support from a rescue team.
- I told you, he's not a victim.

58
00:07:40,990 --> 00:07:42,050
I repeat.

59
00:07:42,490 --> 00:07:44,320
Requesting immediate support
from the rescue team!

60
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:49,930
(The Killer’s House)

61
00:07:50,430 --> 00:07:52,000
- Here he comes.
- He's here.

62
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:53,600
Don't come too close.

63
00:07:53,730 --> 00:07:56,140
- Let us through!
- Is it true a large settlement was paid?

64
00:07:56,140 --> 00:07:58,200
Why are you denying the use of a weapon
during the assault?

65
00:07:58,400 --> 00:08:00,370
Did you even give the victim
a proper apology?

66
00:08:00,710 --> 00:08:02,740
I've cooperated fully
with the police investigation.

67
00:08:03,380 --> 00:08:04,940
I apologize for the concern I've caused.

68
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:07,810
Jeffrey, please give us a statement
on the situation!

69
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:11,950
Excuse me. One moment, everyone!

70
00:08:13,620 --> 00:08:16,820
This case has been closed
with no charges filed.

71
00:08:17,420 --> 00:08:19,490
That's enough, all right?

72
00:08:19,690 --> 00:08:22,230
But the CCTV footage confirms the assault,
doesn't it?

73
00:08:23,530 --> 00:08:25,560
Please have some faith
in the police investigation.

74
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:30,370
- We're coming through. Make way!
- Jeffrey, do you admit to using a weapon?

75
00:08:31,870 --> 00:08:32,870
Hey, kill the music.

76
00:08:34,670 --> 00:08:37,380
Please have some faith
in the police investigation.

77
00:08:38,140 --> 00:08:40,610
Gosh, you were so impressive.

78
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:43,680
You're a total lifesaver.

79
00:08:44,450 --> 00:08:48,550
No, really. I had faith in you
from the very beginning.

80
00:08:51,660 --> 00:08:54,830
You only got away with it
because it's your first offense.

81
00:08:55,130 --> 00:08:56,760
Assault, drugs.

82
00:08:57,630 --> 00:09:01,700
One little spark, and this all
blows up in your face. Got it?

83
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:04,400
Yes, that's what I'm paying you
the big bucks for.

84
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:06,610
That's what you're paying for?

85
00:09:08,970 --> 00:09:10,110
Am I your friend?

86
00:09:13,650 --> 00:09:14,650
Sir.

87
00:09:24,890 --> 00:09:26,260
(Park Min Seo: Medical bill payment)

88
00:09:26,260 --> 00:09:27,960
(Guardian Park Han Jun,
please come to the admin office)

89
00:09:33,870 --> 00:09:36,370
(Jaeil Hospital)

90
00:09:47,910 --> 00:09:49,520
I just stopped by
the administration office.

91
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:53,020
Have you still not heard from him?

92
00:09:53,850 --> 00:09:55,820
No, not yet.

93
00:10:02,330 --> 00:10:04,460
You must have been going through a lot.

94
00:10:05,530 --> 00:10:06,530
Mr. Park,

95
00:10:07,330 --> 00:10:10,970
I can get my hands on
the treatment for Batten disease.

96
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:14,670
But the procedures for getting it
are extremely strict.

97
00:10:16,180 --> 00:10:18,240
Since it's a treatment for
a rare genetic disorder,

98
00:10:18,740 --> 00:10:20,710
you're aware the bidding costs are high,
aren't you?

99
00:10:21,250 --> 00:10:24,880
I know. I'll get the money,
no matter what it takes.

100
00:10:27,950 --> 00:10:29,420
I should tell you upfront.

101
00:10:30,290 --> 00:10:31,990
You have to be prepared
for the side effects.

102
00:10:33,130 --> 00:10:34,260
What do you mean, side effects?

103
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:38,000
You didn't know?
Didn't you say your wife is a doctor?

104
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:40,300
I haven't told her yet.

105
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:44,440
Just a moment.

106
00:10:49,580 --> 00:10:50,610
Would you take a look at this?

107
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:54,480
It's a treatment for genetic disorders
being developed by a domestic company.

108
00:10:56,010 --> 00:10:58,650
It has also shown a positive response
in patients with Batten disease.

109
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:02,090
It also recently passed clinical trials
on children.

110
00:11:02,650 --> 00:11:04,620
Now, it's still in the approval phase,

111
00:11:05,220 --> 00:11:07,360
but if you were to invest
in this early project,

112
00:11:07,660 --> 00:11:09,060
you won't have to get on the waiting list,

113
00:11:09,390 --> 00:11:11,500
and I'll do what I can
to get you the medication quickly.

114
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:17,000
How's our Min Seo doing?

115
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:21,170
She might look fine,
but her motor skills have worsened.

116
00:11:22,170 --> 00:11:24,380
And she keeps forgetting things
that happened just yesterday.

117
00:11:28,610 --> 00:11:31,720
- What? Dad!
- Hey, Min Seo.

118
00:11:38,460 --> 00:11:40,530
The phone you have dialed
is currently switched off.

119
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:43,800
You will be redirected to their voicemail
after the beep.

120
00:11:44,030 --> 00:11:45,960
- Call charges may apply...
- Darn you...

121
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:50,540
(Please, I'm begging you, call me.)

122
00:11:50,540 --> 00:11:52,600
(Moon Se Guk, Serom Biotech)

123
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:19,330
(Happy Citizens, A Just Prosecution)

124
00:12:27,210 --> 00:12:30,110
- Are you coming straight from the scene?
- Yes.

125
00:12:33,850 --> 00:12:37,250
(Prosecutor Cha Yi Yeon)

126
00:12:37,250 --> 00:12:38,780
Good work out there, Prosecutor Cha.

127
00:12:39,790 --> 00:12:43,120
The detectives did the hard work.
Ours is just beginning.

128
00:12:46,330 --> 00:12:47,660
These are the documents for approval,
right?

129
00:12:48,090 --> 00:12:51,730
- Yes. But are you leaving already?
- I need to be on it from the very start.

130
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:56,500
And please clip any articles from tonight
so I can review them in the morning.

131
00:12:57,340 --> 00:12:58,340
Got it.

132
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:07,480
Looks like things will be hectic again
for a while.

133
00:13:09,410 --> 00:13:12,350
But don't you think the case will be
reassigned anyway?

134
00:13:12,650 --> 00:13:16,720
Come on. Have you forgotten?
Any case she sets her sights on is ours.

135
00:13:17,090 --> 00:13:20,960
With her background
as the youngest daughter of Sejin Group,

136
00:13:21,130 --> 00:13:23,000
why does she make things
so hard for herself?

137
00:13:23,530 --> 00:13:26,000
I'm sure being passed over for promotion
was a big blow.

138
00:13:26,060 --> 00:13:29,430
What's the big deal?
She won't be a prosecutor forever.

139
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:33,740
She could just coast for a while,
get a boost from her father,

140
00:13:34,210 --> 00:13:37,740
and land a cushy job as chief counsel
on the Sejin Group's legal team.

141
00:13:38,780 --> 00:13:39,880
I'd say it's 1 of 2 things.

142
00:13:40,610 --> 00:13:42,780
She doesn't want to
tarnish her father's name.

143
00:13:43,050 --> 00:13:44,150
What's that supposed to mean?

144
00:13:44,220 --> 00:13:46,850
All conglomerate heirs are
put on the elite track.

145
00:13:47,090 --> 00:13:50,560
Parents are always sizing each other up
in the center of attention.

146
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:51,920
The comparisons must be brutal.

147
00:13:56,130 --> 00:13:57,400
So what's the second reason?

148
00:13:57,830 --> 00:13:59,100
I guess it's just her nature.

149
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:01,930
She's someone who wants to right wrongs.

150
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:11,510
I didn't mishear back at the crime scene,
did I?

151
00:14:13,180 --> 00:14:16,820
That guy, Lee Woo Gyeom,
he knew your name.

152
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,120
And?

153
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:21,320
Do you two happen to know each other?

154
00:14:21,650 --> 00:14:24,760
Detective Gong, expand the search area
at the scene for now.

155
00:14:25,220 --> 00:14:28,990
- Yes, ma'am.
- I'll ask Lee Woo Gyeom myself.

156
00:14:35,270 --> 00:14:36,270
Hello.

157
00:14:41,270 --> 00:14:43,710
We'll be seeing a lot of each other,
so let's skip the pleasantries.

158
00:14:44,310 --> 00:14:45,880
How did you know who I was?

159
00:14:46,550 --> 00:14:48,450
I've seen you in an article before.

160
00:14:48,980 --> 00:14:51,780
- I have a pretty good memory.
- That's good.

161
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:54,190
Because I have
quite a few questions for you.

162
00:14:55,390 --> 00:14:56,460
Back at the crime scene,

163
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:59,460
you told me you were
treating the victim, correct?

164
00:14:59,730 --> 00:15:02,560
Yes. He was a terminal cancer patient.

165
00:15:03,330 --> 00:15:06,100
By the time he came to me,
the cancer had already spread quite a bit.

166
00:15:06,630 --> 00:15:07,670
So I...

167
00:15:08,270 --> 00:15:09,630
Let's save that story for later.

168
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:11,040
What?

169
00:15:12,070 --> 00:15:13,240
But you're the one who asked.

170
00:15:15,410 --> 00:15:17,340
I was just confirming whether or not
you intended to kill him.

171
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:20,510
All right, then.
Let's go through this step-by-step.

172
00:15:21,150 --> 00:15:23,720
What was all that stuff
in the refrigerator?

173
00:15:24,980 --> 00:15:26,080
You already saw what was in there.

174
00:15:28,620 --> 00:15:32,490
I'm asking you why you did it.
I want a clear explanation.

175
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:41,230
It's for research purposes.

176
00:15:42,570 --> 00:15:44,670
Research.

177
00:15:46,470 --> 00:15:47,540
The dismembered bodies.

178
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:52,580
What kind of research?

179
00:15:56,310 --> 00:15:57,920
You're asking because you're
actually curious, right?

180
00:15:58,220 --> 00:16:01,090
- Why do you ask?
- The detectives didn't believe me.

181
00:16:02,450 --> 00:16:05,690
I'll have to hear it to judge, won't I?
What was the research?

182
00:16:07,090 --> 00:16:09,690
I was developing a cure
for incurable diseases.

183
00:16:10,230 --> 00:16:11,300
Incurable diseases?

184
00:16:11,660 --> 00:16:13,870
A cure that can overcome any disease.

185
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:15,470
That's the kind of cure I was making.

186
00:16:16,230 --> 00:16:18,940
But to see if the cure actually works,

187
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:23,380
- I needed a living human body.
- So, like a clinical trial?

188
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:26,610
Yes. So I conducted experiments on people.

189
00:16:29,750 --> 00:16:32,580
Did you kill them during the experiments,
or...

190
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:35,850
did you experiment on them
after you killed them?

191
00:16:39,020 --> 00:16:41,660
Since they died
after I administered the cure...

192
00:16:42,260 --> 00:16:43,260
No, that's not it.

193
00:16:43,660 --> 00:16:45,800
I think I administered the cure
after I killed them.

194
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:52,070
It really depends on the situation.

195
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:53,840
It's case-by-case.

196
00:16:55,770 --> 00:16:56,780
Fine.

197
00:16:57,840 --> 00:17:00,050
That's for the autopsy to determine.

198
00:17:01,550 --> 00:17:02,950
How many victims are there?

199
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,380
Prosecutor Cha.

200
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:08,450
How long are you going to keep asking
these pointless questions?

201
00:17:09,620 --> 00:17:12,520
I'm telling you I was developing a cure.
Aren't you curious about that?

202
00:17:13,390 --> 00:17:14,560
In an investigation,

203
00:17:15,030 --> 00:17:17,130
the first step is to establish
the scale of the crime.

204
00:17:19,330 --> 00:17:20,500
Now, tell me.

205
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:24,770
The DNA analysis suggests
there are more victims.

206
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:26,640
Where are these people?

207
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:28,340
I'm sure they're around somewhere.

208
00:17:28,910 --> 00:17:29,910
Did you kill them?

209
00:17:30,140 --> 00:17:31,380
Come on, Prosecutor Cha.

210
00:17:32,110 --> 00:17:34,880
- You can't just keep demanding answers.
- I'm asking you, did you kill them?

211
00:17:36,850 --> 00:17:39,150
- It's the same as not killing them.
- Lee Woo Gyeom!

212
00:17:40,420 --> 00:17:43,360
We found more than five dismembered bodies
at the scene.

213
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:45,760
And...

214
00:17:46,420 --> 00:17:49,060
they are the bodies
of the missing victims, aren't they?

215
00:18:01,910 --> 00:18:03,110
Here, take a look at this.

216
00:18:11,920 --> 00:18:13,890
(17-17)

217
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:16,860
You know the answer, right?

218
00:18:17,660 --> 00:18:20,290
Just tell me what you see.

219
00:18:21,290 --> 00:18:23,660
Stop wasting my time. What's your point?

220
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:26,260
You're the one wasting time.

221
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:30,170
If we can't get on the same page,
how can this investigation get anywhere?

222
00:18:36,840 --> 00:18:38,710
- Zero.
- Exactly.

223
00:18:41,810 --> 00:18:45,380
I killed 17 people,
but in return, I saved the world.

224
00:18:45,480 --> 00:18:47,350
So in the end, the death toll is zero.

225
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:54,660
It's as if I didn't kill a single person.

226
00:19:15,410 --> 00:19:17,020
(Police)

227
00:19:17,080 --> 00:19:18,080
Yes, Prosecutor Cha.

228
00:19:18,580 --> 00:19:21,850
- We found them.
- Lee Woo Gyeom has 17 victims.

229
00:19:22,050 --> 00:19:24,520
What? Seventeen victims?

230
00:19:25,790 --> 00:19:28,890
At the crime scene of Lee Woo Gyeom,
who was arrested yesterday,

231
00:19:28,890 --> 00:19:33,060
seven bodies have been discovered
out of a total of seventeen victims.

232
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:37,500
Police are determining the time of death
and identify the bodies...

233
00:19:40,810 --> 00:19:41,810
Good.

234
00:19:46,440 --> 00:19:48,580
- Min Seo.
- Dad,

235
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:51,050
Where have you been?

236
00:19:56,390 --> 00:19:57,390
Here you go.

237
00:20:04,130 --> 00:20:05,160
Let me know when you're heading out.

238
00:20:05,730 --> 00:20:06,730
Okay.

239
00:20:20,210 --> 00:20:21,350
So, Min Seo...

240
00:20:23,210 --> 00:20:24,380
You love dolls that much?

241
00:20:25,020 --> 00:20:27,920
- Yes.
- I know you love your dolls,

242
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:30,020
but it's also good to go outside...

243
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:31,690
- and play with your friends.
- But I don't have any friends.

244
00:20:33,590 --> 00:20:35,760
I was only at school for a week.

245
00:20:37,460 --> 00:20:38,460
I know.

246
00:20:40,830 --> 00:20:42,070
It's okay, Dad.

247
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:45,470
Min Seo,

248
00:20:46,070 --> 00:20:49,070
once you're all better,
you're going to make so many friends.

249
00:20:49,370 --> 00:20:53,450
Dad will send you to middle school,
high school, and...

250
00:20:54,210 --> 00:20:55,810
I'll even send you abroad to study.

251
00:20:56,610 --> 00:20:58,980
- Really?
- Of course I mean it.

252
00:20:59,580 --> 00:21:02,450
Pinky promise? Promise.

253
00:21:07,260 --> 00:21:08,960
- Dad.
- Yes?

254
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:11,200
Can't we all...

255
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:13,470
live together again...

256
00:21:14,730 --> 00:21:16,000
like we used to?

257
00:21:20,610 --> 00:21:21,610
Of course.

258
00:21:22,740 --> 00:21:23,910
Of course we will.

259
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:44,430
(Reporter Jo Woo Cheol, Daehan Ilbo News)

260
00:21:45,900 --> 00:21:48,230
Well, look who it is.
Long time no see.

261
00:21:50,170 --> 00:21:51,270
(It's not too late for the Prosecution...)

262
00:21:51,340 --> 00:21:52,370
(to stop the false charges and listen.)

263
00:22:03,680 --> 00:22:04,680
Reporter Jo.

264
00:22:06,120 --> 00:22:07,120
Well, hey!

265
00:22:11,060 --> 00:22:13,060
- How long has it been?
- It's been way too long.

266
00:22:13,120 --> 00:22:14,830
- Have a seat.
- No, please, you have a seat.

267
00:22:22,270 --> 00:22:24,300
- Here, I haven't touched this one.
- No, it's fine.

268
00:22:24,700 --> 00:22:25,870
I had something on the way.

269
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:30,680
So, Reporter Jo.

270
00:22:31,210 --> 00:22:34,550
Why did you suddenly leave the paper
when you were doing so well?

271
00:22:35,850 --> 00:22:36,920
Don't get me started.

272
00:22:37,420 --> 00:22:39,950
Remember last year when I clashed
with the Prosecution?

273
00:22:40,350 --> 00:22:44,960
Well, after that, I lost all my sources,
got hit with a lawsuit, and was terrified.

274
00:22:45,390 --> 00:22:48,890
I still have to support my wife, right?
So I just started my own thing.

275
00:22:50,660 --> 00:22:52,200
So, how's it working out for you?

276
00:22:52,830 --> 00:22:55,300
Well, it's a relief not having to
walk on eggshells around the higher-ups,

277
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:57,470
but the money's just not there.

278
00:23:02,340 --> 00:23:05,610
I've been following the Jeffrey case.
He's a famous producer, isn't he?

279
00:23:05,710 --> 00:23:09,080
I never imagined you'd be the one
to take his case.

280
00:23:10,250 --> 00:23:13,420
A man's got to feed his family.

281
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:17,490
So here I am.

282
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:20,090
So, Mr. Park.

283
00:23:20,860 --> 00:23:22,160
How about you and I...

284
00:23:22,430 --> 00:23:24,560
work on something
that'll help us both get by?

285
00:23:25,430 --> 00:23:26,430
A case?

286
00:23:31,670 --> 00:23:33,140
You've seen the news
about Lee Woo Gyeom, right?

287
00:23:33,540 --> 00:23:37,440
The serial killer who murdered 17 people?
He wants to hire you.

288
00:23:38,510 --> 00:23:40,710
The retainer has nine zeroes.

289
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:47,520
Man, for that kind of money,
he could hire a big-name law firm.

290
00:23:47,590 --> 00:23:49,250
He'd have a much better shot
with them than with me.

291
00:23:49,990 --> 00:23:53,930
We can't have that.
I'm the one connecting you to him,

292
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:56,030
so I need to get my finder's fee.

293
00:23:56,790 --> 00:23:57,830
Just kidding.

294
00:23:58,430 --> 00:23:59,730
Apparently, Lee Woo Gyeom has a reason...

295
00:24:00,930 --> 00:24:02,830
why it absolutely has to be you.

296
00:24:03,970 --> 00:24:04,970
And what reason is that?

297
00:24:07,070 --> 00:24:10,040
He said you'd know what it's about
if I mentioned Moon Se Guk.

298
00:24:12,180 --> 00:24:15,610
I can get you the treatment
for Batten disease.

299
00:24:16,050 --> 00:24:17,920
It's just that the procedure
is incredibly complicated.

300
00:24:24,420 --> 00:24:25,690
He knows Moon Se Guk?

301
00:24:26,360 --> 00:24:28,090
Yes. I heard it
from Lee Woo Gyeom himself.

302
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:33,900
How in the world does he know Moon Se Guk?

303
00:24:34,370 --> 00:24:36,400
He said Moon Se Guk
was one of his victims.

304
00:24:41,610 --> 00:24:43,040
He killed him? Lee Woo Gyeom did?

305
00:24:43,840 --> 00:24:47,480
- Sir, did you call for a driver? Sir.
- Seriously.

306
00:24:47,550 --> 00:24:49,980
But why would Lee Woo Gyeom
kill Moon Se Guk?

307
00:24:56,650 --> 00:24:58,920
He wouldn't tell me the details.

308
00:25:03,430 --> 00:25:04,430
Damn it.

309
00:25:09,430 --> 00:25:12,170
Arrange a meeting for me with him.

310
00:25:20,410 --> 00:25:24,020
Section Chief Bang, get all the case files
on Lee Woo Gyeom from Detective Gong.

311
00:25:24,250 --> 00:25:27,090
But I heard they'll pick which department
gets that case after the meeting today.

312
00:25:27,150 --> 00:25:29,850
Exactly. And after that meeting,
it's going to be ours.

313
00:25:33,830 --> 00:25:34,890
What was that?

314
00:25:35,560 --> 00:25:37,700
I told you yesterday
I was going to land this case.

315
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:41,530
I meant that I understood.

316
00:25:47,770 --> 00:25:51,680
Manager Lee, schedule an interrogation
with Lee Woo Gyeom for this afternoon.

317
00:25:51,940 --> 00:25:53,040
Yes, right away.

318
00:25:56,680 --> 00:25:58,380
- Prosecutor Cha.
- Yes?

319
00:25:58,520 --> 00:26:00,850
He has a meeting scheduled
with his attorney this afternoon.

320
00:26:02,750 --> 00:26:03,790
His attorney?

321
00:26:05,890 --> 00:26:06,960
Yes, come on in.

322
00:26:12,530 --> 00:26:14,430
I was just heading out. Let's go.

323
00:26:15,130 --> 00:26:17,640
I need to talk to you before the meeting.

324
00:26:19,140 --> 00:26:20,140
All right, have a seat.

325
00:26:30,620 --> 00:26:31,780
About the Lee Woo Gyeom case...

326
00:26:32,380 --> 00:26:33,580
Please assign it to me.

327
00:26:34,820 --> 00:26:36,450
What's the big rush?

328
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:38,960
I did all the legwork
to bring this case in myself.

329
00:26:39,660 --> 00:26:43,800
I spent my whole paycheck schmoozing
the detectives at Guam Police Station.

330
00:26:43,900 --> 00:26:47,270
Give me a break.
Since when you worry about money?

331
00:26:48,330 --> 00:26:49,330
I know you missed the promotion,

332
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:51,100
and that's why
you're acting like this, but...

333
00:26:52,100 --> 00:26:56,070
Prosecutor Cha, don't focus on cases,
but your peer reviews.

334
00:26:56,670 --> 00:26:59,810
Those reviews aren't because
I did something wrong.

335
00:27:00,580 --> 00:27:03,250
I know. They're all just jealous.

336
00:27:03,820 --> 00:27:07,120
Some crazy kid just walks away
from her dad's perfectly good company,

337
00:27:07,320 --> 00:27:10,790
rejects a match with a conglomerate heir,
and doesn't care what her superiors think.

338
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:12,760
You live your life saying
whatever is on your mind.

339
00:27:13,060 --> 00:27:14,130
How could they not be jealous?

340
00:27:14,260 --> 00:27:17,930
That's exactly why I should take it.
I have no conflicts, so I would be clean.

341
00:27:18,300 --> 00:27:19,300
No.

342
00:27:20,160 --> 00:27:21,530
If only for the media attention,

343
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:23,400
it has to be someone with
Prosecutor Kim's experience.

344
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:26,340
Even with Park Han Jun
as the defense attorney?

345
00:27:27,670 --> 00:27:28,670
What?

346
00:27:29,610 --> 00:27:32,540
- Park Han Jun? From the CIU?
- You know the one.

347
00:27:32,940 --> 00:27:35,780
He won landmark unfair labor,
harassment, and injury cases...

348
00:27:35,780 --> 00:27:37,880
for the first time in Korea.

349
00:27:38,650 --> 00:27:41,890
He'd eat Prosecutor Kim for lunch.

350
00:27:42,450 --> 00:27:44,490
Wait, why would Park Han Jun
even take this case?

351
00:27:45,620 --> 00:27:47,490
What, is he that desperate for money?

352
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:50,390
That's not the point.

353
00:27:51,300 --> 00:27:53,430
Director Oh, this is a serial murder case.

354
00:27:53,700 --> 00:27:55,870
If we can't get the death penalty,
whoever prosecutes will be crucified.

355
00:27:55,870 --> 00:27:57,470
No one is going to want to touch it.

356
00:27:58,470 --> 00:28:01,870
Don't just play hot potato with the case
until it blows up in our faces.

357
00:28:02,510 --> 00:28:03,510
Let me take the case.

358
00:28:04,140 --> 00:28:07,180
Listen, you can't take on a case like this
out of some misguided sense of justice.

359
00:28:07,250 --> 00:28:09,650
Are my peer reviews going to be
any different next year?

360
00:28:10,380 --> 00:28:13,850
Not unless I solve a major case myself...
There's no other way, is there?

361
00:28:14,320 --> 00:28:15,890
But what if our department...

362
00:28:16,590 --> 00:28:19,020
had the prosecutor who finally took down
Park Han Jun?

363
00:28:19,620 --> 00:28:21,760
Then you, the director who mentored me.

364
00:28:22,360 --> 00:28:25,100
Wouldn't you be setting off fireworks
instead of a bomb?

365
00:28:26,460 --> 00:28:27,700
Please, assign me the case.

366
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:39,880
(1 Ha 3, 1941)

367
00:28:51,260 --> 00:28:54,390
This is Attorney Park Han Jun.

368
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:56,990
And this is Mr. Lee Woo Gyeom.

369
00:28:58,000 --> 00:28:59,000
A pleasure.

370
00:29:01,230 --> 00:29:04,840
To give you a brief summary of the case...

371
00:29:04,900 --> 00:29:06,040
You killed Moon Se Guk?

372
00:29:08,540 --> 00:29:10,780
Aren't you supposed to be
the composed one here?

373
00:29:11,240 --> 00:29:12,780
You're very impatient.

374
00:29:13,040 --> 00:29:15,950
Comes with the territory.
You hesitate, you get stabbed in the back.

375
00:29:18,780 --> 00:29:19,780
Lee Woo Gyeom.

376
00:29:20,480 --> 00:29:21,620
Did you really...

377
00:29:23,820 --> 00:29:25,090
kill Moon Se Guk?

378
00:29:28,360 --> 00:29:30,190
Yes, I did. Why?

379
00:29:35,230 --> 00:29:36,230
Then...

380
00:29:36,870 --> 00:29:37,870
The cure.

381
00:29:38,600 --> 00:29:40,340
The cure that Moon Se Guk had...

382
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:43,570
- What did you do with it?
- What are you talking about?

383
00:29:44,740 --> 00:29:46,240
All I did was kill him.

384
00:29:46,540 --> 00:29:47,550
What?

385
00:29:51,850 --> 00:29:53,920
But the fact that
you're looking for a cure...

386
00:29:54,820 --> 00:29:56,120
It must mean someone you know is very ill.

387
00:29:56,190 --> 00:29:59,020
- Don't play games with me...
- Is it a family member?

388
00:30:00,020 --> 00:30:01,630
Seeing how desperate you are...

389
00:30:01,930 --> 00:30:03,890
Could it be the daughter
you had so late in life?

390
00:30:07,470 --> 00:30:09,670
You're more naive than I thought.

391
00:30:10,070 --> 00:30:11,670
No wonder you got scammed
out of 2 million dollars.

392
00:30:15,270 --> 00:30:16,270
You...

393
00:30:17,240 --> 00:30:18,840
What was your relationship
with Moon Se Guk?

394
00:30:19,910 --> 00:30:24,650
Tell me exactly what you know. And...
Where is the cure that Moon Se Guk had?

395
00:30:25,180 --> 00:30:26,420
I'm telling you, there's no such thing.

396
00:30:26,820 --> 00:30:28,820
He said he completed the clinical trials.
He was clear.

397
00:30:29,790 --> 00:30:30,790
It has to exist.

398
00:30:35,190 --> 00:30:36,190
Attorney Park.

399
00:30:37,560 --> 00:30:39,660
There is no cure for Batten disease.

400
00:30:40,770 --> 00:30:43,600
Especially for someone like Min Seo,
who's already showing early symptoms.

401
00:30:44,670 --> 00:30:46,970
Death within a few years
is the only possible outcome.

402
00:30:49,810 --> 00:30:50,810
Mr. Park.

403
00:30:51,540 --> 00:30:53,180
Why don't we all sit down?

404
00:31:07,260 --> 00:31:08,260
Attorney Park.

405
00:31:09,490 --> 00:31:10,830
There's no need to get so worked up.

406
00:31:11,630 --> 00:31:13,030
Let's have a real conversation.

407
00:31:13,700 --> 00:31:15,500
Moon Se Guk may have lied to you,

408
00:31:16,170 --> 00:31:17,170
but I, for one,

409
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:19,440
can cure Min Seo's disease.

410
00:31:21,010 --> 00:31:22,010
But...

411
00:31:24,110 --> 00:31:25,180
How do you...

412
00:31:26,180 --> 00:31:28,010
even know my daughter's name?

413
00:31:32,120 --> 00:31:34,090
Since you came all this way today,

414
00:31:34,420 --> 00:31:35,850
I'll give you a retainer
of one million dollars.

415
00:31:37,120 --> 00:31:38,960
And if you get me out of here,

416
00:31:39,360 --> 00:31:41,390
- I'll give you another million dollars.
- Lee Woo Gyeom.

417
00:31:42,590 --> 00:31:44,600
Didn't I tell you to stop playing games?

418
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:48,230
You're a lawyer.
Is being scammed all you've ever known?

419
00:31:49,100 --> 00:31:52,800
I have the money, if not the cure.
You don't believe me?

420
00:31:53,740 --> 00:31:54,740
Reporter Jo.

421
00:31:57,370 --> 00:31:58,710
He's for real, Attorney Park.

422
00:32:02,550 --> 00:32:04,420
No need to be so grateful.

423
00:32:05,580 --> 00:32:07,750
It's the money
you got scammed out of anyway.

424
00:32:13,690 --> 00:32:15,290
Let's just say I believe you.

425
00:32:15,990 --> 00:32:17,290
But what if I just take the money...

426
00:32:18,560 --> 00:32:19,930
and refuse to represent you?

427
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:26,140
I doubt that's going to happen.

428
00:32:27,510 --> 00:32:29,940
Once you meet the people I've cured,

429
00:32:31,640 --> 00:32:33,810
you'll be the one coming to me.

430
00:32:35,950 --> 00:32:36,950
Lee Woo Gyeom.

431
00:32:38,920 --> 00:32:42,290
What makes you so confident?

432
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:45,920
They all had incurable diseases,

433
00:32:46,660 --> 00:32:47,930
and I'm the one who cured them.

434
00:33:03,840 --> 00:33:05,710
(Taesan Bank deposit: 1 million dollars,
From Lee Woo Gyeom)

435
00:33:13,050 --> 00:33:16,150
A million dollars in one go. I'm jealous.

436
00:33:17,290 --> 00:33:20,060
I should've studied harder in school.

437
00:33:22,230 --> 00:33:23,230
Reporter Jo.

438
00:33:25,160 --> 00:33:26,700
What's the deal between
you and Lee Woo Gyeom?

439
00:33:27,970 --> 00:33:29,100
I already told you.

440
00:33:29,370 --> 00:33:31,840
I make the introduction,
and I get a commission.

441
00:33:32,800 --> 00:33:34,970
I think it was about a week
before he was arrested.

442
00:33:35,310 --> 00:33:37,170
Lee Woo Gyeom contacted me directly.

443
00:33:37,510 --> 00:33:38,740
A week before he was arrested?

444
00:33:39,240 --> 00:33:41,610
I thought he was crazy at first,
of course.

445
00:33:42,250 --> 00:33:46,180
But he claimed he was curing people
of incurable diseases...

446
00:33:46,380 --> 00:33:47,890
and told me to go find his patients.

447
00:33:48,290 --> 00:33:51,560
And there was survivor,
right there in front of me.

448
00:33:51,790 --> 00:33:54,160
And then, the money hit my account.

449
00:33:55,290 --> 00:33:57,860
I figured, "This is meant to be,"
and I just went with it.

450
00:33:59,430 --> 00:34:02,930
- You saw this for yourself, Reporter Jo?
- Yes. I'm the one who found them.

451
00:34:03,370 --> 00:34:04,940
That's why I ended up writing the article.

452
00:34:07,270 --> 00:34:08,270
Is that right?

453
00:34:09,970 --> 00:34:12,280
All right.
First, let's go meet this survivor.

454
00:34:13,210 --> 00:34:15,650
(Guam Police Station)

455
00:34:15,850 --> 00:34:20,020
It looks like most of the evidence
from the scene will be admissible.

456
00:34:20,280 --> 00:34:22,550
The forensics lab called this morning.

457
00:34:23,090 --> 00:34:27,120
They found a common substance
in all the victims' bodies.

458
00:34:27,890 --> 00:34:32,200
Apparently, it's very similar
to a compound...

459
00:34:32,260 --> 00:34:33,630
from a new drug just developed in the US.

460
00:34:34,060 --> 00:34:38,440
It's just strange that Lee Woo Gyeom
seems to have used it first.

461
00:34:38,600 --> 00:34:43,110
The guy must've been brilliant.
He was top of his class in med school.

462
00:34:43,740 --> 00:34:46,380
But then, the car accident happened,
and it was all over just like that.

463
00:34:47,180 --> 00:34:49,610
He was in a vegetative state for 3 years,
you said?

464
00:34:49,910 --> 00:34:52,150
That's right.
He only had two family members,

465
00:34:52,620 --> 00:34:54,450
and his mother passed away
while he was in that state.

466
00:34:54,520 --> 00:34:57,890
So he was left with no next of kin.

467
00:34:58,590 --> 00:35:02,790
And this...
This is the victims' profiles.

468
00:35:03,290 --> 00:35:05,000
I think you should take a look at these.

469
00:35:05,360 --> 00:35:08,370
(Summary of victims' criminal records)

470
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:11,400
They all have criminal records?

471
00:35:11,770 --> 00:35:12,770
Yes.

472
00:35:15,740 --> 00:35:16,840
(Guam Medical Center)

473
00:35:16,910 --> 00:35:20,980
In that case...
What kind of treatment was it?

474
00:35:21,580 --> 00:35:23,010
Did he explain that to you?

475
00:35:23,080 --> 00:35:27,650
He did, but what would I know
about any of that?

476
00:35:27,920 --> 00:35:31,320
Then what made you decide
to go through with it?

477
00:35:33,190 --> 00:35:37,490
My husband was in so much pain.
I just told him to do whatever he wanted.

478
00:35:38,260 --> 00:35:41,800
Excuse me, do you know anyone else
who got the treatment before your husband?

479
00:35:41,870 --> 00:35:46,570
Yes. I was referred by Sang Woo's Mom.
We used to work together.

480
00:35:47,140 --> 00:35:51,380
She said her son was cured
of incurable polio.

481
00:35:51,940 --> 00:35:52,940
In that case,

482
00:35:54,180 --> 00:35:56,080
could I get her contact information?

483
00:35:56,380 --> 00:36:01,390
There's the owner of the hair salon
right next door to where I used to work.

484
00:36:01,650 --> 00:36:04,760
She and Sang Woo's mom have been friends
for a long time.

485
00:36:05,920 --> 00:36:08,690
You can probably find out from her
if you go there.

486
00:36:08,760 --> 00:36:09,860
(Lee Woo Gyeom: Murderer or Savior?)

487
00:36:10,260 --> 00:36:13,100
Have you met any other survivors
besides him?

488
00:36:13,300 --> 00:36:17,070
Besides Lee Chang Se who I just met,
it's all just been hearsay.

489
00:36:17,530 --> 00:36:18,870
What? So you wrote this article...

490
00:36:19,370 --> 00:36:20,540
without even meeting them?

491
00:36:21,210 --> 00:36:23,370
A guy's got to eat.

492
00:36:23,610 --> 00:36:26,280
An article's merit is measured in clicks,
isn't it?

493
00:36:27,640 --> 00:36:28,650
There was a time...

494
00:36:29,310 --> 00:36:32,220
when you were all about social justice
and fighting the Prosecution.

495
00:36:32,280 --> 00:36:34,520
Now it looks like all you're fighting
is your own conscience.

496
00:36:35,950 --> 00:36:39,560
Gosh, that's a great line.
You should comment that on the article.

497
00:36:39,620 --> 00:36:40,990
I bet it would go viral.

498
00:36:42,390 --> 00:36:44,830
- Goodness.
- Sure. I'll comment that it's all lies.

499
00:36:44,900 --> 00:36:49,070
Come on. The other one sounded better.
You should post that one, word for word.

500
00:36:50,500 --> 00:36:53,170
Cut the crap and tell me already.

501
00:36:53,840 --> 00:36:55,840
Besides the victims
whose dismembered bodies turned up,

502
00:36:56,270 --> 00:36:57,270
the other ten...

503
00:36:58,340 --> 00:37:01,310
- Where did you dump their bodies?
- If you look at it from another angle,

504
00:37:01,850 --> 00:37:03,380
that's not what's important
here at all.

505
00:37:05,820 --> 00:37:08,290
You killed 17 people.

506
00:37:08,820 --> 00:37:11,590
You should see it as me saving them,
not killing them.

507
00:37:14,590 --> 00:37:17,130
Is that really what's important to you?

508
00:37:17,760 --> 00:37:21,470
Not the fact that all your victims
had criminal records?

509
00:37:25,270 --> 00:37:26,800
You figured that out sooner
than I expected.

510
00:37:27,570 --> 00:37:31,040
So at trial, you were planning on saying,
"I only killed bad guys."

511
00:37:31,180 --> 00:37:33,080
"Please let me off the hook?" Is that it?

512
00:37:33,280 --> 00:37:36,410
Please. That's so childish.
I have some self-respect.

513
00:37:36,810 --> 00:37:39,920
Stop posturing. This is vigilantism.

514
00:37:40,320 --> 00:37:41,820
You really think that's going to hold up
in court?

515
00:37:46,190 --> 00:37:50,190
Prosecutor Cha.
I saved patients with incurable diseases.

516
00:37:50,990 --> 00:37:53,800
Their deaths were a necessary sacrifice
to save others.

517
00:37:53,800 --> 00:37:55,200
So when exactly were you going to ask me
about that?

518
00:37:55,870 --> 00:37:58,200
Even if you saved 100 or 1,000 people,

519
00:37:58,540 --> 00:38:00,900
killing someone means you're a murderer,
doesn't it?

520
00:38:04,580 --> 00:38:08,280
Isn't that simpler math than 17 minus 17?

521
00:38:10,080 --> 00:38:11,350
Are we done here?

522
00:38:11,680 --> 00:38:12,680
Sit down.

523
00:38:13,880 --> 00:38:16,150
You don't get up before I do.

524
00:38:16,750 --> 00:38:19,720
If you wanted to be treated like a human,
you should've acted like one.

525
00:38:21,230 --> 00:38:23,590
Don't get cocky,
you murdering son of a gun.

526
00:38:23,930 --> 00:38:24,930
I apologize.

527
00:38:27,360 --> 00:38:28,370
Such a self-righteous ass.

528
00:38:29,230 --> 00:38:31,940
- What was that?
- Nothing.

529
00:38:34,200 --> 00:38:35,210
Forget it.

530
00:38:35,540 --> 00:38:37,410
You don't have to tell me
where you dumped them.

531
00:38:37,840 --> 00:38:41,810
I've already identified all the victims,
and I have more than enough to indict you.

532
00:38:42,510 --> 00:38:44,880
I couldn't care less
about your so-called "cure."

533
00:38:46,120 --> 00:38:48,520
You can go ahead
and run your mouth in court.

534
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:55,990
You're just taking your bad mood out on me
because it's hot.

535
00:39:00,330 --> 00:39:02,270
If you insist on being this stubborn,

536
00:39:03,370 --> 00:39:04,800
you're the one walking away with nothing.

537
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:24,520
We have to find those dump sites,
no matter what.

538
00:39:25,190 --> 00:39:27,790
What? You're saying
Lee Woo Gyeom won't cooperate?

539
00:39:28,130 --> 00:39:30,330
He's just trying to play games with us.

540
00:39:31,560 --> 00:39:33,600
If we just let him
spoon-feed us the answers,

541
00:39:33,900 --> 00:39:35,230
it'll be humiliating.

542
00:39:35,700 --> 00:39:37,000
But Prosecutor Cha,

543
00:39:37,200 --> 00:39:38,970
if you could persuade him,
we could find the victims much sooner...

544
00:39:39,040 --> 00:39:40,940
Persuade him?
I ought to be chewing him out.

545
00:39:41,410 --> 00:39:44,040
We'll find them on our own,
and then we'll indict him.

546
00:39:44,410 --> 00:39:46,680
- Got it?
- Yes, ma'am. Understood.

547
00:39:47,040 --> 00:39:49,180
I'll expand the search parameters
and get started.

548
00:39:51,920 --> 00:39:53,220
I think we've checked everything here.

549
00:39:53,280 --> 00:39:55,450
- Let's move on to the next alley.
- You guys check that way.

550
00:39:55,520 --> 00:39:56,620
We'll go this way.

551
00:39:58,120 --> 00:40:00,060
Excuse me, ma'am.
We'd like to ask you a few questions.

552
00:40:00,660 --> 00:40:02,460
We're from the Guam Police Station.

553
00:40:02,560 --> 00:40:03,760
- Do you have CCTV?
- Are any cameras installed?

554
00:40:04,090 --> 00:40:05,160
At our shop...

555
00:40:05,530 --> 00:40:06,860
By any chance,
could we check your CCTV footage?

556
00:40:07,130 --> 00:40:08,170
- May we see your CCTV footage?
- One moment.

557
00:40:08,230 --> 00:40:09,230
Just a moment.

558
00:40:13,500 --> 00:40:15,710
(Bora Hair Salon)

559
00:40:17,940 --> 00:40:19,710
Why are you looking for Sang Woo's Mom?

560
00:40:21,410 --> 00:40:25,620
I heard that
Sang Woo made a full recovery.

561
00:40:25,720 --> 00:40:27,320
- Really?
- Yes.

562
00:40:27,780 --> 00:40:29,090
No way, how did that happen?

563
00:40:29,450 --> 00:40:30,750
So, that's why...

564
00:40:31,390 --> 00:40:32,660
Her home address...

565
00:40:33,290 --> 00:40:35,360
or her new phone number...
Do you happen to have it?

566
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:39,030
She only told me she'd contact me
once she got settled.

567
00:40:39,100 --> 00:40:41,100
She didn't give me any other details.

568
00:40:41,230 --> 00:40:44,330
Sang Woo's Mom had it really tough
when she was here.

569
00:40:44,640 --> 00:40:48,370
The money she made for his medical fees.
It was nowhere near enough.

570
00:40:49,210 --> 00:40:51,740
And she couldn't look after Sang Woo
while she was at work, you know.

571
00:40:52,340 --> 00:40:56,380
Look, what about places Sang Woo's Mom
or Sang Woo used to frequent?

572
00:40:56,550 --> 00:40:59,420
Or someone who was like family to them,
like you?

573
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:01,750
Seriously, anything at all.
Please just tell us.

574
00:41:01,890 --> 00:41:04,290
I don't know if this will help. Hold on.

575
00:41:04,290 --> 00:41:07,560
Sang Woo really loved to draw, you know.

576
00:41:08,560 --> 00:41:10,590
Here it is, right here.
Take a look at this.

577
00:41:10,790 --> 00:41:11,860
He was so talented, wasn't he?

578
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:22,340
- Over there.
- That way.

579
00:41:25,940 --> 00:41:27,210
Haven't seen them.

580
00:41:28,350 --> 00:41:29,350
Do you...

581
00:41:38,490 --> 00:41:39,660
No, I haven't seen them.

582
00:41:45,730 --> 00:41:48,070
The serial murder suspect
and a former medical student.

583
00:41:48,130 --> 00:41:50,470
We're here at the scene where police
are searching for more of his victims.

584
00:41:50,800 --> 00:41:54,640
Public outcry is growing
over the massive police mobilization.

585
00:41:55,270 --> 00:41:58,080
They say it's a waste of manpower,
all based on the suspect's single word.

586
00:41:58,140 --> 00:41:59,840
- Reporter Jo.
- Yes?

587
00:41:59,840 --> 00:42:00,980
The victims.

588
00:42:02,050 --> 00:42:03,280
Do you have any of them identified?

589
00:42:04,150 --> 00:42:05,780
The police aren't releasing any names yet.

590
00:42:07,220 --> 00:42:08,550
In that case, I need you to...

591
00:42:09,520 --> 00:42:11,860
do some digging on your own.

592
00:42:12,690 --> 00:42:13,790
Okay, I'll do that.

593
00:42:21,770 --> 00:42:23,070
You've had a long day, Prosecutor Cha.

594
00:42:23,500 --> 00:42:27,170
- Welcome back.
- Lee Woo Gyeom's psych eval results.

595
00:42:28,370 --> 00:42:29,910
- They're in?
- Yes.

596
00:42:29,910 --> 00:42:31,310
(Guam Central Dist. Prosecutors' Office)

597
00:42:31,310 --> 00:42:33,510
(Polygraph Test Results)

598
00:42:34,950 --> 00:42:38,420
Mr. Lee Woo Gyeom.
Is it true that you murdered people?

599
00:42:39,980 --> 00:42:40,980
Yes.

600
00:42:41,220 --> 00:42:44,090
Is it false that you treated people
and saved their lives?

601
00:42:44,820 --> 00:42:45,820
No.

602
00:42:51,190 --> 00:42:53,260
(First Trial: No deception indicated,
Second Trial: No deception indicated)

603
00:42:53,730 --> 00:42:55,500
Are you sure
this test was administered correctly?

604
00:42:55,630 --> 00:42:59,440
Yes. They said his responses were normal.
They even ran a different test pattern,

605
00:42:59,700 --> 00:43:03,070
and the results were still the same.
And the funny thing is,

606
00:43:03,270 --> 00:43:05,080
they said he was happy that he passed.

607
00:43:10,850 --> 00:43:12,450
Why are you still just searching?

608
00:43:12,980 --> 00:43:15,720
Lee Woo Gyeom is using the location
of the bodies as a bargaining chip.

609
00:43:15,950 --> 00:43:17,290
Just play along and wrap this up.

610
00:43:17,520 --> 00:43:19,720
If I do that, he'll lead me
by the nose for the entire trial.

611
00:43:19,920 --> 00:43:21,660
The public is in an uproar
because we can't find the victims.

612
00:43:22,230 --> 00:43:23,330
I understand.

613
00:43:23,930 --> 00:43:25,060
I'll think it over.

614
00:43:33,440 --> 00:43:34,870
This isn't a confession.

615
00:43:35,640 --> 00:43:37,210
You've written your own heroic epic.

616
00:43:38,780 --> 00:43:40,810
Depending on
whether you believe me or not...

617
00:43:41,450 --> 00:43:42,910
That's what changes the genre.

618
00:43:43,050 --> 00:43:46,880
Whatever the genre, the ending
to this story is the death penalty.

619
00:43:59,030 --> 00:44:00,030
Fine.

620
00:44:01,200 --> 00:44:04,630
- Since we're on the subject, tell me.
- Tell me what?

621
00:44:04,630 --> 00:44:06,340
You said you treated people.

622
00:44:06,970 --> 00:44:08,040
So tell me all about it.

623
00:44:11,540 --> 00:44:12,710
Are you serious?

624
00:44:13,110 --> 00:44:14,610
Want to start with the cure?

625
00:44:15,480 --> 00:44:16,480
Actually, no.

626
00:44:17,110 --> 00:44:19,080
Start with how you made it.

627
00:44:22,990 --> 00:44:24,090
Are you going to tell me or not?

628
00:44:30,260 --> 00:44:34,200
The cure...
It all began with a dying potted plant.

629
00:44:36,570 --> 00:44:39,500
I poured some leftover liquid
from my research into the pot,

630
00:44:43,340 --> 00:44:45,310
and when I checked on it the next day,

631
00:44:46,510 --> 00:44:48,380
the dead flower had come back to life.

632
00:44:49,750 --> 00:44:51,550
That's the cure?

633
00:44:52,050 --> 00:44:53,050
Yes.

634
00:44:54,020 --> 00:44:55,050
Go on.

635
00:44:56,520 --> 00:44:58,520
Next, I took that cure,

636
00:44:59,420 --> 00:45:00,890
and put it in a fish tank.

637
00:45:02,090 --> 00:45:04,290
My dead goldfish came back to life.

638
00:45:05,530 --> 00:45:09,800
Then there was a cat with an injured leg.
It recovered so well that...

639
00:45:11,130 --> 00:45:12,270
it was jumping high again in no time.

640
00:45:18,110 --> 00:45:20,810
At this point, aren't you curious too?

641
00:45:22,310 --> 00:45:23,850
If it works on humans.

642
00:45:28,050 --> 00:45:30,050
That's when you started killing people?

643
00:45:30,820 --> 00:45:32,720
I told you, it wasn't murder.
It was research.

644
00:45:34,860 --> 00:45:38,830
- How long did you plan to keep this up?
- But the thing is...

645
00:45:39,860 --> 00:45:41,770
Humans are definitely a lot harder.

646
00:45:42,470 --> 00:45:44,070
How long...

647
00:45:45,600 --> 00:45:47,240
did you plan on going around
killing people?

648
00:45:51,810 --> 00:45:52,880
Seventeen people.

649
00:45:53,580 --> 00:45:54,710
That was it.

650
00:45:56,350 --> 00:45:57,350
Why?

651
00:45:58,210 --> 00:45:59,620
Because the experiment was a success.

652
00:46:01,990 --> 00:46:03,990
Who was the last victim?

653
00:46:05,690 --> 00:46:06,860
Hong Jae Gwang.

654
00:46:07,590 --> 00:46:08,790
Are you sure about that?

655
00:46:09,860 --> 00:46:10,860
Yes.

656
00:46:13,930 --> 00:46:15,830
You'll understand
when you see him for yourself.

657
00:46:16,870 --> 00:46:19,670
It's a little complicated
to explain in words.

658
00:46:22,740 --> 00:46:25,310
(Guam District Prosecutors' Office)

659
00:46:35,290 --> 00:46:36,350
Okay.

660
00:46:37,450 --> 00:46:39,560
Why didn't you resist arrest?

661
00:46:40,660 --> 00:46:42,030
You could've gotten away.

662
00:46:42,760 --> 00:46:44,890
I was planning to turn myself in
after treating my patient,

663
00:46:45,730 --> 00:46:46,930
Lee Chang Se, anyway.

664
00:46:49,270 --> 00:46:50,270
Turn yourself in?

665
00:46:51,370 --> 00:46:54,670
I was just waiting for the right moment
to prove my abilities.

666
00:46:55,470 --> 00:46:57,310
You didn't catch me.

667
00:46:58,440 --> 00:47:01,650
Why do you insist on proving it,

668
00:47:01,980 --> 00:47:04,180
specifically through a trial?

669
00:47:04,510 --> 00:47:07,750
Because that's the most official,
indisputable way.

670
00:47:14,090 --> 00:47:15,990
That's how I can be forgiven for my sins.

671
00:47:19,030 --> 00:47:21,600
Not forgiveness. Condemnation.

672
00:47:23,630 --> 00:47:24,730
We'll see about that.

673
00:47:26,340 --> 00:47:27,340
Okay.

674
00:47:29,940 --> 00:47:30,940
All right.

675
00:47:31,740 --> 00:47:34,440
I've heard enough about the history
of your so-called cure.

676
00:47:35,280 --> 00:47:36,280
Now,

677
00:47:38,050 --> 00:47:39,950
it's your turn to help me out.

678
00:47:40,850 --> 00:47:43,250
Where did you dump the remaining victims?

679
00:47:49,060 --> 00:47:50,860
On the mid-slope of Mount Cheonggye,

680
00:47:51,630 --> 00:47:54,630
facing the river,
at the 100-meter mark.

681
00:48:02,370 --> 00:48:04,070
Be more thorough!

682
00:48:05,440 --> 00:48:07,180
- Bring it here.
- Yes, sir.

683
00:48:07,180 --> 00:48:08,980
- Let's go.
- All right.

684
00:48:19,490 --> 00:48:21,930
I heard there's something called
a plea bargain in trials.

685
00:48:22,730 --> 00:48:27,000
- Yes.
- Well, I don't want a lighter sentence.

686
00:48:29,400 --> 00:48:30,970
I want to make a different kind of deal.

687
00:48:32,100 --> 00:48:33,470
First, I'll need you...

688
00:48:34,470 --> 00:48:38,740
to help me so that
I can prove my abilities in court.

689
00:48:45,480 --> 00:48:49,950
(Liked by 99_guswn and others)

690
00:48:51,890 --> 00:48:53,160
Okay, thank you.

691
00:48:56,560 --> 00:48:57,560
Attorney Park.

692
00:48:59,160 --> 00:49:01,260
No matter how much I dig,
I'm coming up empty.

693
00:49:01,970 --> 00:49:04,370
I'm thinking,
since Sang Woo's leg was injured,

694
00:49:04,670 --> 00:49:06,700
maybe he just drew those pictures
at home by himself?

695
00:49:08,400 --> 00:49:09,670
We have to find him.

696
00:49:10,710 --> 00:49:11,710
Right.

697
00:49:20,180 --> 00:49:23,220
- Hello?
- Mr. Park? Hi, it's the hair salon.

698
00:49:23,290 --> 00:49:24,290
Right.

699
00:49:39,100 --> 00:49:40,200
So this is the place.

700
00:49:47,840 --> 00:49:48,850
Is anyone here?

701
00:49:54,320 --> 00:49:56,920
You're going to demonstrate your abilities
in court?

702
00:49:58,620 --> 00:50:00,360
Because I've been indulging you,

703
00:50:01,320 --> 00:50:02,430
you're getting pretty cocky, aren't you?

704
00:50:06,500 --> 00:50:08,460
Aren't you the one who's excited,
Prosecutor Cha?

705
00:50:09,230 --> 00:50:13,340
Thrilled this case will make your career,
aren't you?

706
00:50:16,510 --> 00:50:20,580
Or is it thanks to your powerful father
that you think you're above it all?

707
00:50:24,180 --> 00:50:26,380
This punk.
You've really crossed the line today.

708
00:50:57,150 --> 00:50:59,220
- Mom.
- Yes, sweetie?

709
00:51:12,900 --> 00:51:14,530
Hey! Bring me a shovel!

710
00:51:25,240 --> 00:51:26,240
I found it!

711
00:51:28,910 --> 00:51:31,450
Over here! I found it!

712
00:51:31,710 --> 00:51:33,680
- Get a shovel over here!
- We found it!

713
00:51:33,680 --> 00:51:34,980
- Right here!
- We found it!

714
00:51:35,250 --> 00:51:38,660
- Hey, get the gear over here now!
- Over here! We found it!

715
00:51:39,020 --> 00:51:41,060
- We found it!
- We found it!

716
00:51:41,220 --> 00:51:43,460
- On my way!
- We found it!

717
00:51:43,460 --> 00:51:44,860
- I said it's over here.
- Yes, coming!

718
00:51:44,930 --> 00:51:46,430
- Here! Over here!
- Hey, hurry up!

719
00:51:46,430 --> 00:51:48,460
I found it! It's here, right here!

720
00:51:53,800 --> 00:51:55,070
I think it's Hong Jae Gwang.

721
00:51:55,840 --> 00:51:57,670
The body's been completely drained
of blood.

722
00:52:03,710 --> 00:52:05,680
You'll see for yourself once you check.

723
00:52:06,350 --> 00:52:09,090
It's complicated to explain in words,
you see.

724
00:52:14,320 --> 00:52:16,130
Moon Se Guk lied,

725
00:52:18,290 --> 00:52:19,360
but as for me,

726
00:52:20,830 --> 00:52:22,500
I can cure Min Seo's illness.

727
00:52:23,300 --> 00:52:24,700
Every single one of them...

728
00:52:26,140 --> 00:52:27,670
was treated by me.

729
00:52:41,990 --> 00:52:43,820
Now it's your turn to cross the line,
Prosecutor Cha.

730
00:52:45,660 --> 00:52:46,990
Come over to my side.

731
00:52:47,890 --> 00:52:49,760
I will personally show you in court.

732
00:52:51,430 --> 00:52:52,530
How I can save a life...

733
00:52:54,730 --> 00:52:56,130
without so much as a scalpel.

734
00:53:03,410 --> 00:53:05,410
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
